Step 1: Identify the Total Revenue from the income statement.  
• Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70

Step 2: Determine the total assets at the beginning and at the end from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Total Assets = 28,000,000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 39,772,748.32

Step 3: Calculate the average total assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
• = (28,000,000.00 + 39,772,748.32) / 2  
• = 67,772,748.32 / 2  
• = 33,886,374.16

Step 4: Compute the Total Asset Turnover Ratio using the formula:  
  Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• = 28,572,608.70 / 33,886,374.16  
• ≈ 0.8429  

Rounded to two decimal places, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.84.

Thus, the solution in the requested format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.84"
  }
}
